TITLE: Handling Abort Signals in Tool Execution (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to handle abort signals during tool execution.  The `execute` function receives an `abortSignal` as the second parameter, which can be forwarded to asynchronous operations like `fetch` to cancel them if the agent's execution is aborted. This allows for graceful cancellation of long-running tasks within tools.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/agents/adding-tools.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { createTool } from "@mastra/core/tools";
import { z } from "zod";

const agent = new Agent({
  name: "Weather agent",
  tools: {
    weather: createTool({
      id: "Get Weather Information",
