TITLE: RAG Implementation Example TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates a basic RAG implementation: initializing a document, creating chunks using a recursive strategy, generating embeddings using OpenAI's embedding model, storing them in a PgVector database, and querying for similar chunks. It requires the 'ai', '@ai-sdk/openai', '@mastra/pg', '@mastra/rag', and 'zod' dependencies, as well as a PostgreSQL connection string in the environment variables. The code returns similar chunks from the vector database based on a query vector.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/ja/docs/rag/overview.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { embedMany } from "ai";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { PgVector } from "@mastra/pg";
import { MDocument } from "@mastra/rag";
import { z } from "zod";

// 1. Initialize document
const doc = MDocument.fromText(`Your document text here...`);

// 2. Create chunks
const chunks = await doc.chunk({
  strategy: "recursive",
  size: 512,
  overlap: 50,
});

// 3. Generate embeddings; we need to pass the text of each chunk
const { embeddings } = await embedMany({
  values: chunks.map(chunk => chunk.text),
  model: openai.embedding("text-embedding-3-small"),
});

// 4. Store in vector database
const pgVector = new PgVector(process.env.POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING);
await pgVector.upsert({
  indexName: "embeddings",
  vectors: embeddings,
}); // using an index name of 'embeddings'

// 5. Query similar chunks
const results = await pgVector.query({
  indexName: "embeddings",
  queryVector: queryVector,
  topK: 3,
}); // queryVector is the embedding of the query

console.log("Similar chunks:", results);
```

