TITLE: Document Processing
DESCRIPTION: Processes a document by creating an `MDocument` instance and then chunking it into smaller parts.  The `chunk` method is used with a 'recursive' strategy, specifying chunk size, overlap, and separator. It also extracts keywords from each chunk, enhancing the metadata for filtering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/ja/examples/rag/usage/filter-rag.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const doc = MDocument.fromText(`The Impact of Climate Change on Global Agriculture...`);

const chunks = await doc.chunk({
  strategy: 'recursive',
  size: 512,
  overlap: 50,
  separator: '\n',
  extract: {
    keywords: true,  // Extracts keywords from each chunk
  },
});
```

