TITLE: Workflow Run State Monitoring with run.watch() in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use the `run.watch()` function to subscribe to state changes in a Mastra workflow run. It imports the `Workflow` class, creates a new workflow and run, and then uses `run.watch()` to log results and active paths to the console. The `unsubscribe` function is used to stop monitoring state changes after the workflow is started.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/reference/workflows/watch.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Workflow } from "@mastra/core/workflows";

const workflow = new Workflow({
  name: "document-processor"
});

const run = workflow.createRun();

// Subscribe to state changes
const unsubscribe = run.watch(({results, activePaths}) => {
  console.log('Results:', results);
  console.log('Active paths:', activePaths);
});

// Run the workflow
await run.start({
  input: { text: "Process this document" }
});

// Stop watching
unsubscribe();
```

