TITLE: Processing Documents into Chunks
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to process a document into smaller chunks. It uses the `MDocument.fromText` method to create a document from the given text and then chunks it using the `chunk` method. The chunking strategy is set to "recursive" with a size of 512 and an overlap of 50. The separator is set to newline character.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/ja/examples/rag/usage/cot-rag.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const doc = MDocument.fromText(
  `The Impact of Climate Change on Global Agriculture...`,
);

const chunks = await doc.chunk({
  strategy: "recursive",
  size: 512,
  overlap: 50,
  separator: "\n",
});
```

