TITLE: Updating Voice Provider Configuration using voice.updateConfig() in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to update the configuration of a voice provider (specifically OpenAIRealtimeVoice) at runtime using the `updateConfig()` method. It initializes a voice provider, connects to the service, updates the voice and turn detection settings, and then speaks using the new configuration.

Dependencies: @mastra/voice-openai-realtime
Parameters: options (Record<string, unknown>) - Configuration options to update (voice, turn_detection).
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/ja/reference/voice/voice.updateConfig.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { OpenAIRealtimeVoice } from "@mastra/voice-openai-realtime";

