TITLE: Calling Agent from Command Line (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code demonstrates how to call an agent directly from the command line. It imports the `mastra` instance and retrieves the `weatherAgent` using `mastra.getAgent("weatherAgent")`. It then calls the `generate` method on the agent with the query "What is the weather in London?" and logs the agent's response to the console. This provides a way to interact with agents programmatically without relying on REST API endpoints.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/getting-started/installation.mdx#_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { mastra } from "./mastra";

async function main() {
  const agent = await mastra.getAgent("weatherAgent");

  const result = await agent.generate("What is the weather in London?");

  console.log("Agent response:", result.text);
}

main();
```

