TITLE: Defining Workflow Steps in Mastra (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code defines two steps in a Mastra workflow. The first step doubles an input value, and the second step increments the result if the first step was successful.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/workflows/overview.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const stepOne = new Step({
  id: "stepOne",
  outputSchema: z.object({
    doubledValue: z.number(),
  }),
  execute: async ({ context }) => {
    const doubledValue = context.triggerData.inputValue * 2;
    return { doubledValue };
  },
});

const stepTwo = new Step({
  id: "stepTwo",
  execute: async ({ context }) => {
    const doubledValue = context.getStepResult(stepOne)?.doubledValue;
    if (!doubledValue) {
      return { incrementedValue: 0 };
    }
    return {
      incrementedValue: doubledValue + 1,
    };
  },
});
```

