TITLE: Running Agent from Command Line (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to invoke a Mastra agent from the command line using TypeScript. It imports the `mastra` object, retrieves the `weatherAgent`, and then calls the `generate` method. The response is logged to the console. This requires the Mastra SDK and tsx to be installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/ja/docs/getting-started/installation.mdx#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { mastra } from "./mastra";

async function main() {
