TITLE: Registering Custom API Route in Mastra - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to register a custom API route within a Mastra instance. It defines a GET route at `/my-custom-route` with a handler that accesses the Mastra instance and returns a JSON response. This demonstrates how to extend the server with custom endpoints that interact with the Mastra core functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/ja/docs/deployment/server.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Mastra } from "@mastra/core";
import { registerApiRoute } from "@mastra/core/server";

export const mastra = new Mastra({
  server: {
    apiRoutes: [
      registerApiRoute("/my-custom-route", {
        method: "GET",
        handler: async (c) => {
          // you have access to mastra instance here
          const mastra = c.get("mastra");

          // you can use the mastra instance to get agents, workflows, etc.
          const agents = await mastra.getAgent("my-agent");

          return c.json({ message: "Hello, world!" });
        },
      }),
    ],
  },
  // Other configuration options
});
```

